cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on RDMA performance and congestion control protocols. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of multiple applications coexisting. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is relevant as the proposed solution, Justitia, is a software-only, host-based solution. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the tradeoff between performance isolation and work conservation. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also relevant as the paper focuses on improving the latency and throughput of RDMA-based applications.
